{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"<mo>","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mo","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n    <ol>\n        <li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element\">MathML Reference</a></strong>\n\n        \n            </li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/maction\">&lt;maction&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/math\">&lt;math&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/menclose\">&lt;menclose&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/merror\">&lt;merror&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mfenced\">&lt;mfenced&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mfrac\">&lt;mfrac&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mi\">&lt;mi&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mmultiscripts\">&lt;mmultiscripts&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mn\">&lt;mn&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mo\">&lt;mo&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mover\">&lt;mover&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mpadded\">&lt;mpadded&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mphantom\">&lt;mphantom&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mroot\">&lt;mroot&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mrow\">&lt;mrow&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/ms\">&lt;ms&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mspace\">&lt;mspace&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msqrt\">&lt;msqrt&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mstyle\">&lt;mstyle&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msub\">&lt;msub&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msubsup\">&lt;msubsup&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msup\">&lt;msup&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtable\">&lt;mtable&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtd\">&lt;mtd&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtext\">&lt;mtext&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtr\">&lt;mtr&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/munder\">&lt;munder&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/munderover\">&lt;munderover&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/semantics\">&lt;semantics&gt;</a></li>\n        \n\n        \n    </ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The MathML <code>&lt;mo&gt;</code> element represents an operator in a broad sense. Besides operators in strict mathematical meaning, this element also includes \"operators\" like parentheses, separators like comma and semicolon, or \"absolute value\" bars.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"attributes","title":"Attributes","isH3":false,"content":"<p>This element's attributes include the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes\">global MathML attributes</a>.</p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"accent\">accent</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      If the operator is used as an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/munder\">under</a>- or <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mover\">overscript</a> this attribute specifies whether the operator should be treated as an accent.\n      Allowed values are <code>true</code> or <code>false</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"fence\">fence</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      There is no visual effect for this attribute, but it specifies whether the operator is a fence (such as parentheses).\n      Allowed values are <code>true</code> or <code>false</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"lspace\">lspace</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The amount of space before the operator (see <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Attribute/Values#lengths\">length</a> for values and units). The constant <code>thickmathspace</code> (5/18em) is the default value.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"maxsize\">maxsize</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>If <code>stretchy</code> is <code>true</code>, this attribute specifies the maximum size of the operator. Allowed values are:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li><code>infinity</code></li>\n      <li>an arbitrary <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Attribute/Values#lengths\">length</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"minsize\">minsize</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>If <code>stretchy</code> is <code>true</code>, this attribute specifies the minimum size of the operator. Allowed values are:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li><code>infinity</code></li>\n      <li>an arbitrary <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Attribute/Values#lengths\">length</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"movablelimits\">movablelimits</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Specifies whether attached under- and overscripts move to sub- and superscript positions when <code>displaystyle</code> is <code>false</code>.\n      Allowed values are either <code>true</code> or <code>false.</code>\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"rspace\">rspace</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The amount of space after the operator (see <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Attribute/Values#lengths\">length</a> for values and units). The constant <code>thickmathspace</code> (5/18em) is the default value.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"separator\">separator</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      There is no visual effect for this attribute, but it specifies whether the operator is a separator (such as commas).\n      Allowed values are <code>true</code> or <code>false</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"stretchy\">stretchy</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Specifies whether the operator stretches to the size of the adjacent element.\n      Allowed values are <code>true</code> or <code>false</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"symmetric\">symmetric</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      If <code>stretchy</code> is <code>true</code>, this attribute specifies whether the operator should be vertically symmetric around the imaginary math axis (centered fraction line).\n      The default value is <code>true</code> if <strong>stretchy</strong> is set to <code>true</code> and otherwise <code>false</code>. Allowed values are <code>true</code> or <code>false</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>math</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mrow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>5<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>+<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>5<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mrow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mrow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span> [ <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- default form value: prefix --&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mrow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span> 0 <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span> ; <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- default form value: infix --&gt;</span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span> 1 <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mrow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span> ) <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- default form value: postfix --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mrow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>math</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/mathml-core/#operator-fence-separator-or-accent-mo","title":"MathML Core"}],"query":"mathml.elements.mo"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"mathml.elements.mo","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mo/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"gecko-specific_notes","title":"Gecko-specific notes","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>Starting with Gecko 16.0 (Firefox 16.0 / Thunderbird 16.0 / SeaMonkey 2.13) the default values for <code>lspace</code> and <code>rspace</code> have been corrected to match the MathML3 specification. They now default to the constant <code>thickmathspace</code> (5/18em).</li>\n  <li>Any <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/MathML3/chapter3.html#presm.lbattrs\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">linebreaking</a> or <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/MathML3/chapter3.html#presm.lbindent.attrs\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">indentation attributes</a> are not implemented yet. See <a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=534962\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;534962</a>.</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Attributes","id":"attributes"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The MathML <mo> element represents an operator in a broad sense. Besides operators in strict mathematical meaning, this element also includes \"operators\" like parentheses, separators like comma and semicolon, or \"absolute value\" bars.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-08T14:50:14.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"<mo>","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch"},{"title":"<mo>","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/mathml/element/mo","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/mathml/element/mo/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/d3a04bcdd16434b613b132fb488235ce44355891","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML","title":"MathML"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element","title":"MathML element reference"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mo","title":"<mo>"}],"pageTitle":"<mo> - MathML | MDN","noIndexing":false}}